Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[i'nɔ:məsli]
*phó từ
 ■to lớn, khổng lồ
 ■vô cùng, hết sức

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
enormously
▸ adverb
1an enormously important factor: VERY, extremely, really, exceedingly, exceptionally, tremendously, immensely, hugely; singularly, particularly, eminently; informal terrifically, awfully, terribly, seriously, desperately, ultra, damn, damned; Brit.informal ever so, well, dead, jolly; N. Amer.informal real, mighty, darned; informal, dated frightfully.
2prices vary enormously: CONSIDERABLY, greatly, very much, a great deal, a lot.
Opposites
slightly.
